    "body": "### Problem\n\nBackticks are concealed as if it's a code. Example in the `tips.txt`:\n```help\nBreaking up restoring the position:\n\t't\tgo to the line previously at the top of the window\n\tzt\tscroll to move this line to the top of the window\n\t`s\tjump to the original position of the cursor\n```\n\n<img width=\"742\" height=\"112\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0a71985a-6213-4929-8274-121d59bb1eca\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:help restore-position\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n<img width=\"749\" height=\"114\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0ef4fd4f-1987-4416-a079-fbb7c39e9331\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.2.316\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux x86_64, Linux 6.19.11-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.17.0 (94e7c887)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\npacman, Arch extra repository",
